Colombia Coal-Mine Accident Traps Eight Workers, Tiempo Reports

-- B y   H e a t h e r   W a l s h
-- 
2011-05-17T18:16:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-17/colombia-coal-mine-accident-traps-eight-workers-tiempo-reports.html
Eight Colombian workers are trapped
following a collapse at a coal mine today, newspaper  El Tiempo 
reported on its website, citing unidentified rescue workers.  The cave-in this morning in western  Colombia  near the city
of Cali at the Lomagorda mine trapped workers who apparently are
safe and awaiting rescue from firefighters, the Bogota-based
daily newspaper reported.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Heather Walsh at 
 hlwalsh@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at   dcrofts@bloomberg.net  